<p class="text-lg mt-10">
    @class serves as a mechanism to conditionally add class values to an element. The syntax is:
    condition => classes if true || classes if false.
</p>

<div style="background-color: #1d2538;"
     class="mt-10 overflow-x-scroll max-w-sm sm:max-w-7xl border-2 border-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow-xl drop-shadow-lg">
            <pre>
                <code class="language-html -mb-10 -mt-3">
&lt;div ignite="classes"&gt;
    &lt;span @class="largeText => text-3xl || text-lg"&gt;Hello World&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;script&gt;
    function classes() {
        return {
            largeText: true,
        }
    }
&lt;/script&gt;
                </code>
            </pre>
</div>
<div class="my-10 text-lg">
    The code above will result in the following (with further styling added and a couple name changes):
</div>

<div ignite="classes">
    <span @class="largeText => text-3xl || text-lg">Hello World</span>
    <button
            @click="toggleLargeText"
            class="block mt-3 flex-none rounded-md bg-stone-500 px-3.5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-stone-400 focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-stone-500"
    >
        Toggle Large Text
    </button>
</div>

<script nonce="{{@cspNonce}}">
    function classes() {
        return {
            largeText: true,
            toggleLargeText() {
                this.largeText = !this.largeText;
            }
        }
    }
</script>